land, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bollin, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bollin, Cheshire, Eng.":"Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Bollin, Macclesfield, Cheshire, England":"Macclesfield, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1233–1271":"1233–1271","1232–1269":"1232–1269","1256–1298":"1256–1298","1260–1336":"1260–1336","1264–Male":"1264–Deceased","1267–1346":"1267–1346","about 1260":"about 1260","AFT 1267":"after 1267","1264":"1264","1271":"1271","1260":"1260","1336":"1336","1269":"1269","1346":"1346","1267":"1267","1256":"1256","1233":"1233","1298":"1298","1232":"1232","about 1256":"about 1256","about 1264":"about 1264","um 1238":"about 1238","Bollin Fee, Cheshire, England":"Bollin Fee, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Lord of Bollin, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Bollin, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Bollin, Cheshire, Eng.":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Bollin, Macclesfield, Cheshire, England":"Macclesfield, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fitton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (mainly Lancashire):","from Middle English <i>fiton</i>, <i>fittin</i> ‘lie, falsehood’, for a lier or cheat.","possibly a habitational name from Fitton Hall in Leverington, Cambridgeshire, named in Anglo-Scandinavian as ‘settlement by the meadow-land’, from Old English <i>tūn</i> + Old Norse <i>fit</i>, a term denoting grassland on the bank of a river."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hugh","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French name, <i>Hugues</i>, <i>Hugo</i>, of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’. It was originally a short form of various compound names containing this element. This was borne by the aristocracy of medieval France, adopted by the Normans, and introduced by them to Britain. It was consistently one of the most popular boys' names in the Middle Ages in England, but fell out of favour in the 16th century until it was revived in the 20th century. Little Hugh of Lincoln was a child supposed in the Middle Ages to have been murdered by Jews in about  1255 , a legend responsible for several outbursts of anti-Semitism at various times. The story is referred to by  Chaucer  in The Prioress's Tale. He is not to be confused with  St Hugh of Lincoln  (  1140–1200 ), bishop of Lincoln (  1186–1200 ), who was noted for his charity and good works, his piety, and his defence of the Church against the State. Since the later Middle Ages <i>Hugh</i> has also been used as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic name Aodh ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Hugh Fitton of Bollin was born in 1233, in Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. He married Mrs. Hugh Fitton. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. He died in 1271, at the age of 38."},"et":{"1233–1271":"1233–1271","1232–1269":"1232–1269","1256–1298":"1256–1298","1260–1336":"1260–1336","1264–Male":"1264–Surnud","1267–1346":"1267–1346","about 1260":"umbes 1260","AFT 1267":"pärast 1267","1264":"1264","1271":"1271","1260":"1260","1336":"1336","1269":"1269","1346":"1346","1267":"1267","1256":"1256","1233":"1233","1298":"1298","1232":"1232","about 1256":"umbes 1256","about 1264":"umbes 1264","um 1238":"umbes 1238","Bollin Fee, Cheshire, England":"Bollin Fee, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lord of Bollin, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bollin, Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bollin, Cheshire, Eng.":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Bollin, Macclesfield, Cheshire, England":"Macclesfield, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1233–1271":"1233–1271","1232–1269":"1232–1269","1256–1298":"125